Exceptions are interesting. The calls are asynchronous so you can't wrap the whole macro in a single try/catch. See node's wiki for an explanation on why this is a problem:<p><a href="https://github.com/joyent/node/wiki/Async-exception-handling" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/joyent/node/wiki/Async-exception-handling</a><p>Node encourages people to create functions like:<p><pre><code>    function(err, x) {
        if(err) handle(err);
    }
</code></pre>
This way they avoid the whole async + try/catch problem. It should be possible to define a macro that does something similar.<p>Avoiding that trap, individual try/catch statements still work fine:<p><pre><code>    (timeout/timeout-macro
     (pn "Hello")
     (try*
      (pn (throw "Throwing up"))
      (catch e (pn (str "There was an error: " e))))
     (pn "World"))</code></pre>
